Preheat your oven to 220°C. Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{18-20%minutes}, turn halfway.

Halve the @halloumi{250%g} lengthways so you have 2 'steaks'. Pop them in a #mixing bowl{}. Add the @mayonnaise{1%tbsp} and coat the halloumi 'steaks' in the mayo on all sides. Mix the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} with the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%Mexican Spice packet} on a #plate{}. Stir in a glug of @olive oil{}. Place the halloumi 'steaks' on the crumbs on the plate, press gently and turn so that all sides of the halloumi are coated in the crumbs.

Lay the halloumi on a baking tray lined with #baking paper{}. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{14-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Remove the root from the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways and thinly slice widthways. Put the @red wine vinegar{12%ml}, @sugar{1/4%tsp} and @olive oil{} in a #bowl{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix together with a #fork{}.

Add the tomatoes to the dressing, toss to coat and set aside. Once the halloumi and chips are cooked, add the baby gem to the dressing. Toss to coat.

Serve the halloumi on plates with the sweet potato fries and salad alongside. Enjoy!